Why pre-ironing required ? 

Pre-pleating before draping a saree is a helpful technique to achieve a neat, structured, and elegant look. It involves creating pleats in the saree fabric beforehand, which makes the draping process smoother and ensures uniform pleats.

One last bridal before #cloudbaby is here! ☁️ This video is filmed on February month🙌🏻

Shivani, my beautiful bride from January 2025, approached me for her wedding and reception makeovers, scheduled for June 5 and 6. For context- I’d worked with her and her family for her engagement and my senior team did their makeovers for pre-engagement rituals. 

I informed Shivani that the dates she was asking were around my due date (actually due was June 4) and that I couldn’t take it. She was kind enough to understand my situation and agreed to book my senior team with whom she had a good experience. 

Both my deliveries were induced, so keeping this in mind, I gave her word that I could do her makeovers if I did not deliver the baby by then. 

✨So, she immediately came up with a backup plan, ie, to have my senior team do the makeovers in case I don’t make it. And our charges were agreed accordingly. 

✅May-June is the peak season in my profession. But I did not accept bookings because I knew it could be risky to be booked. Since Shivani was my previous client and she herself came up with a backup plan, I thought I would do this for her. 

It has never been for money that I go this far, and not for fame. There’s something called “passion” and on top of it my good relationship with my clients. And from within, I know I want to do things until I am able, this time for my bride💖

Ever since I gave a word to Shivani, I’ve been manifesting and praying that I should be able to do her bridals. And I thank the universe for aligning things in my favor. 
Again, thank you Shivani for trusting me and also making this super easy. 

Pregnancy 🤰is always a challenging period to navigate for a working woman and even so for me because I am working past my due date. I can never forget how a client canceled me because I was 7 months pregnant and did not believe I could deliver my best. But thankfully I could pull this off in this 3rd pregnancy for which I am super happy. I do not know if this could have been a possibility any other time, but I am glad it was done well.
